law.text:
The secretary shall:
Appoint county and district boards of health pursuant to KRS 212.020 and 212.850;
Hear and decide appeals from rulings, decisions and actions of the cabinet, where the aggrieved party makes written request therefor to the secretary within thirty (30) days after the ruling, decision or action complained of;
Adopt rules and regulations necessary to regulate and control all matters set forth in KRS 211.180 to the extent the regulation and control of same have not been delegated to some other agency of the Commonwealth and adopt such other rules and regulations as may be necessary to effectuate the purposes of this chapter and any other law relating to public health, except as otherwise provided by law;
Issue or deny hospital licenses;
Approve or disapprove the establishment of proposed hospital service corporations and contracts for hospital service corporations and contracts for hospital services pursuant to KRS 304.32-030;
Approve or disapprove of the establishment of proposed medical service plan corporations and contract for medical services pursuant to KRS 304.32-050, 304.32-140, and 304.32-160;
Enforce the provisions of KRS 311.250, 311.260, 311.375, 311.376.
